<center>'''Level 131''' is the 132<sup>nd</sup> level of the Backrooms.</center><br>{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Level 160 ioi.png|caption=An infamous image of this level.|width=250px}}
'''Level 131''', otherwise nicknamed as '''''Infestation of Irritation''''', appears as an indefinitely expanding forest under a deep blue midnight sky. This forest is out of the ordinary, its essential foliage is a vast combination of plants ranging from all over the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]]. This even include geologically impossible close combinations, such as: banana trees and birch trees growing just a feet beside eachother; tea leaves and palm trees packed together; et cetera.

Although the sky remains in a deep hue of blue,  the plants and the ground appear distinctly orange, and warm in appearance. Despite the deceptive appearance, the environment is wet, humid, and smells foul akin to that unpleasent odor of lifeless fishes. Temparature in this level drastically fluctuates; frequently from 1 degree to harsh 50 degrees Celsius. The reason behind the manifestation of this deceptive color, just like other mysteries, remains unknown, in fact, futher researching, and studies only led to deadends instead of a tolerable answer.

As one ventures deeper into '''Level 131''', note-worthy structures or areas become more and more frequent. These locations can occasionally be safe, even providing, but in other times, they can be environmentally perilous. These structures include '''villages''', '''gardens''', and, rarely, irregular '''apartments'''.

<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Noteworthy Structures/Areas</span>
<tabber>
|-| The Villages=
=== The Villages ===
The most common structures are the villages. Proliferations of invasive vines, and weeds swallowed the villages as a whole. These villages are noticeably disorganised; they do not abide with conventional structure placement grid, hence some houses are located unnaturally far from eachother. The residential units that compose the village are typically built with mangroove wood or dried straw, which creates a major collapsing hazard that can be fatal if one stays incautious. Illumination is minimally present here, albeit, majority of them are either dim, or malfunctioning.

|-| The Apartments=
=== The Apartments ===
The second most common structures are the isolated apartment structures. The blue shade covering the surfaces of its walls and roofs contrasts it in the orange environment. Its general architecture on the exterior is modern, and minimal, however, in the interior, the design is wooden, choatic, and irregular.

Navigation here is inefficient, as some hallways may be 5 centimeters wide; some rooms may be filled with broken, useless items, and furnitures; some stairs may stretch upward too steep to walk onto; et cetara. Illumimatiom is widely present here; each light sources emit a repeated yellow light, and do not flicker unlike those of the villages.

Unfortunately, these apartments are not safe to remain within, as there are many dangerous structural errors that seem almost unavoidable. The engineering of the floors is unstable and loose, which means each wooden planks of the floor usually bent downward, and creak loudly upon the weight of a step. In many cases, they may abruptly collapse into the ground or into the lower floor beneath, which may inflict severe injuries or even death to the ones who fell with it. In rare occasions, the illogically situated broken furnitures would lean then fall over, and the unlucky individuals caught under will have one's cranium area severely damaged with its blunt force trauma and soon may likely die.

To lower the chances of succumbing to these aforementioned hazards:
# One must test the wooden planks of the flooring with a long, and enough strong stick first, before stepping further to detect dangerously loose areas.
# And, one must avoid slightly tilted furnitures.
# But to completely prevent these dangers, obviously do not enter unless one is exhausted and in need of a shelter to have a rest within.

|-| The Gardens=
=== The Gardens ===
The least common, perhaps the rarest areas are the gardens. One should consider oneself lucky if one has accidentally stumbled upon this place, because the gardens are widely regarded by wanderers as the most stable, and resource abundant areas. They are made up of uniform patches containing various edible vegetations, bounded by tall wooden fences. Each crop is held up by poles as if carefully grown by an unseen agricultural proffesional. Atop of each poles, perpectually glowing lanterns are affixed with, providing adequate artificial sunlight for the plants below to grow. Most of these plants include, but not limited to: tomato plants, strawberry shruberries, tea leaves, [[Object 52|Auresuffo]] vines, et cetera.
</tabber></div>
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Entity Presence </div></div>
{{Blurimage|align=right|width=200px|file=Level 160 if.png|caption=An image allegedly depicting one of the houses of the village.|width=250px}}
As what the nickname already indicates, every recorded area of '''Level 131''' is infested with various flying insects, which include, but may not be limited to: mosquitoes, flies, both male and female [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], [[Entity 34|Blood Wasps]], and dragonflies. The most commonly present species are the mosquitoes. These blood suckers would gather around the individual, while others; except [[Entity 34|Blood Wasps]]; would either stick stiff to surfaces, or completely ignore the wanderer.

=== Enlarged Blood-longer ===
Unfortunately, overseers have confirmed the recent reports of large, and grotesquely elongated mosquitoes inhabiting farther regions of the forest as valid, which is supported by sufficient evidence. According to these accounts, their bodies remain slightly bigger than the average, and reasonable size, whilst their limbs are stretched to a disturbing length. Due to these extensions, they are unable to fly as easily as normal mosquitoes; instead, they silently climb tall tree branches, obscuring themselves in elevated areas where visibility is limited. These behaviors are believed to be a method of ambush, which allows them to prey on unsuspecting individuals before feeding on their blood.

To reduce the likelihood of being susceptible to this creature, always make sure to:
# Wear a protective suit to block its stabs,
# Utilize an efficient light source to spot them with more ease,
# And lastly, avoid areas with tall trees, or areas far from structures.
# For an absolute prevention, obviously do not attempt to enter '''Level 131''' unless put in a serious mission to.

</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Human Presence </div></div>
Because of the both aforementioned environmental and entity dangers, it is almost impossible for individuals to remain within '''Level 131''' permanently. Therefore, there are no instances of outposts, bases, and generally habitations. Worsening the matter, [[Phenomenon 15]] affects the level as well. Additionally, before the discovery of this phenomenon had not yet spread, [[Another Dimension Foundation|A.D.F.]] unknowingly began a mission to neutralize the exceeding population of the insects, but, as expected, made no wide changes whatsoever due to the phenomenon.
</div>
