<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Backmail</span>
'''Date:''' 20, 11, 2025<br>'''From:''' ████████████<br>'''To:''' █████████

After what felt like three whole days spent in the most annoying level — Level 131 — I had experienced an encounter with the rumored, and enlarged mosquito itself. For the sake of your deeper research and documentation on this distgusting insect (Yes, I'm gonna give actual informations), I will explain the case in details as precise as I can!

Before this encounter, I was still remaining in the garden while eating its so-called "fresh strawberries." Though my stomach had been hollow for how long god knows, thanks to the cannibal insects devouring eachother like its a dark ritual, my appetite for food was gone — erased! After a long moment of boredom, stress, and overwhelming disgust, I decided to venture outside the garden into unexplored places. I was just trying to satisfy my lingering curiousity. In my mind before going, I reminded myself to not go any farther, but… you know how it went.

I kept going and going, until…

I felt a sharp pain from my back.

Oh boy, here we go again. I guess.

I slapped my back and instantly sensed the pain slipping into almost agony. I looked at my hand that slapped where the pain was, it was partially soaked in blood and… long appendage-esque things were also stuck to it — still twitching, slightly. Understandably, I was taken aback. I checked it again; there were more… of those twitching parts. The pain slowly abated but became extremely itchy. Out of terror, I poured all of my supply [[Object 1|almond water]] (Yes, the supply almond water — it's gone, drained) onto myself to clean up the bloody mess. It did fortunately went clean again. But soon then I finally realized, it was one of those said Enlarged Blood-longers.

To create a far more detailed description of its appearance, I physically had to rearrange the parts to form its what seems like natural appearance. Damn, it was hell disgusting.

I don't want to write anymore, so here's the image of it — DISGUSTING WARNING:

