<div style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;justify-content: space-between;align-items: flex-start;gap: 8px;">
<div style="width: 300px;min-width: 200px;">
=== Entries ===
* While exploring through the seldom, and dense woodland outskirts of the predominant villages within [[Level 112]], the environment may start to shift and change suddenly, likely due to the presence of [[Phenomenon 14|Non-Euclidean geometry]]. Then it will eventually transition and transport the explorer into this level.
* A rare dilapidated, and botanically overgrown section within [[Level 108]] is an entry point into this level. Upon entry, however, the entrance anomalously disappears when the individual looks away, and any form of traces of it being there before are not left behind, thus, it is considered an one-way access to this level.
* In the '''Autumn Town''' settlement of [[Level 124]], there is an unusual chance of finding a moderately decrepit structure, which when one enters it, it strangely, and rapidly transitions the level to this level.
</div>
<div style="width: 350px;min-width: 200px;">
=== Exits ===
<div style="padding-right: 20px;">
* When the general growth of plants starts to gradually dissipate as one goes deeper into the level, No-Clipping through the ground within the said environment is a way of entry to [[Level 135]], and, rarely, its sublevel, [[Level 135.1]].
* An extremely rare variation of the '''Apartments''' appears in a persistent shade of light gray, with bland and minimal architecture, and has an overlaying grainy texture on all over its surfaces, thus largely contrasting it from the surrounding saturated environment. After a minute spent within this structure, one may find oneself lost within [[Level 141]].
* If one encounters an indefinitely stretching road and follows along its path, the individual will be led to [[Level 150]] and any signs of this level, '''Level 131''', behind will subsequently disappear entirely.
* Staying in a rare, unnaturally mountainous, and hollowed tree for an extended period of time may cause the level to gradually transition into [[Level 177]]. Stepping out during this process have been reported to result in the sudden entry to [[The Void]].
</div>
